# AIPlane ‚Äî Monorepo Rules

## What this repo is
AIPlane is a micro-frontend monorepo for AI management tooling, using a host/remote
architecture with Module Federation (Vite Plugin Federation). The dashboard app is the
host and loads other apps as federated remotes at runtime.

Product intent, architecture, and roadmap live in `docs/SPEC.md` ‚Äî read it before
proposing structural changes.

## Tech stack
- Monorepo: pnpm workspaces (`apps/*`) + Turborepo for task orchestration/caching
- Build: Vite + `@originjs/vite-plugin-federation`
- UI: React (18/19), TypeScript (strict mode)
- Lint/format: Biome (not ESLint/Prettier)
- Git hooks: Husky + lint-staged
- Package manager: pnpm 9.x ‚Äî never use npm or yarn commands or lockfiles
- Node: >=18 (see `.nvmrc` for the pinned version)

## Monorepo layout
- `apps/dashboard` ‚Äî host app (port 5173), loads all remotes via Module Federation
- `apps/prompt-manager` ‚Äî remote (port 5174)
- `apps/guardrail` ‚Äî remote (port 5175)
- `apps/user-manager` ‚Äî remote (port 5176)
- `apps/usages-data` ‚Äî remote (port 5177)

Each app is an independent Vite project with its own `package.json`, `tsconfig.json`,
and `vite.config.ts`. Treat each app as a self-contained package (`@repo/<name>`)
unless a change is explicitly cross-cutting.

## Common commands
- `pnpm install` ‚Äî install all workspace deps (run from repo root only)
- `pnpm dev` ‚Äî run all apps in dev mode (needed for federation to work end-to-end)
- `pnpm build` ‚Äî build all apps in Turborepo dependency order
- `pnpm preview` ‚Äî preview production builds
- `pnpm lint` / `pnpm lint:fix` ‚Äî Biome check / autofix
- `pnpm typecheck` ‚Äî TypeScript check across all apps
- `pnpm turbo dev --filter=@repo/dashboard` ‚Äî run a single app by package name

## Working conventions
- This is a pnpm workspace: never add a `node_modules` inside an individual app for a
  dependency that should be hoisted; add deps via pnpm from the correct app directory.
- Respect Turborepo's task graph (`turbo.json`) ‚Äî `build` and `typecheck` depend on
  upstream package builds/typechecks (`^build`, `^typecheck`); don't bypass this by
  scripting around Turbo.
- `admin-dashboard-ui/` is a nested reference repo excluded from Biome and git tracking
  ‚Äî don't edit it as part of this codebase's changes.
- Keep new apps consistent with existing ones: same file layout
  (`index.html`, `src/main.tsx`, `src/App.tsx`, `vite.config.ts`, `tsconfig.json`),
  same Biome/TS config conventions, and register the new app in `pnpm-workspace.yaml`
  (already covered by `apps/*`) and in the dashboard's federation `remotes` if it
  should be loaded by the host.
